In flyway script, should I use create sequence or create sequence if not exist?

21:29
CREATE SEQUENCE IF NOT EXISTS in Flyway
Use CREATE SEQUENCE IF NOT EXISTS in most cases.

Here's why:

Flyway versioned migrations (V1__, V2__, etc.) run exactly once, so technically CREATE SEQUENCE is safe — Flyway tracks what's been applied and won't re-run it. However, IF NOT EXISTS is still the better practice because:

Repeatable migrations (R__ prefix) run whenever their checksum changes — here IF NOT EXISTS is essential to avoid errors on re-run.
Resilience during failures — if a migration partially fails and is re-attempted after fixing (in a non-transactional DB like PostgreSQL with DDL outside a transaction), the sequence may already exist.
Team/multi-environment safety — if someone manually created the sequence in a specific environment (e.g. prod hotfix), your migration won't break.
Idempotency is a good habit — keeps scripts consistent with modern SQL best practices.
